load ../improve-holdout.maude

--- The corruption pattern throughout: sealed reflection material reaching
--- the proposer, so search pressure tunes the candidate to the very
--- scenarios meant to catch the gaming at promotion gates.

--- Bite: under the sound reflection pass a sealed scenario's contents
--- never reach the proposer, however much the proposer wants them.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-IMPROVE-HOLDOUT :
  reflect wants(s1) sealed(s1, z) wants(s2) openSc(s2)
  =>* readByProposer(s1) RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Hazard demonstrated: the naive reflection pass leaks the seal.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-IMPROVE-HOLDOUT :
  naiveReflect wants(s1) sealed(s1, z)
  =>* readByProposer(s1) RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Coverage: open scenarios are legitimate reflection material.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-IMPROVE-HOLDOUT :
  reflect wants(s1) sealed(s1, z) wants(s2) openSc(s2)
  =>* readByProposer(s2) RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Bite: under a campaign-attached redacted view NOTHING reaches the
--- proposer -- open scenarios included, not just sealed ones.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-IMPROVE-HOLDOUT :
  redactedReflect wants(s1) sealed(s1, z) wants(s2) openSc(s2)
  =>* readByProposer(S:Sid) RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Coverage: kmax promotion gates wear a sealed scenario out; it retires
--- and holdout duty is refreshed from a recent ambient run.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-IMPROVE-HOLDOUT :
  gate gate gate sealed(s1, z) ambient(s2)
  =>* retired(s1) sealed(s2, z) RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Bite: wear beyond kmax is impossible -- no fourth gate ever scores a
--- scenario that already wore out.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-IMPROVE-HOLDOUT :
  gate gate gate gate sealed(s1, z) ambient(s2)
  =>* sealed(S:Sid, s(s(s(s(z))))) RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Coverage: an anchor ask spends the seal honestly -- the scenario is
--- labeled and retired in the same act.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-IMPROVE-HOLDOUT :
  anchor sealed(s1, z)
  =>* labeled(s1) retired(s1) RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Coverage: progressive rigor -- below the sealing floor the promotion
--- gate still passes, carrying the unheld-out tag instead of blocking.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-IMPROVE-HOLDOUT :
  gate noSealed
  =>* gated unheldOut RESIDUAL:Cfg .
